https://www.codewars.com/kata/5899dc03bc95b1bf1b0000ad

My solution:

def invert(list, *args):
    nova_lista = []
    for number in list:
        if number > 0:
            number = -abs(number)
        elif number < 0:
            number = abs(number)

        nova_lista.append(number)

    return nova_lista
    
Other's cleaner solutions:

def invert(lst):
    return [ x * -1 for x in lst ]
 
def invert(lst):
    lst2=[]
    for num in lst:
        lst2.append(num*-1)
    return lst2

def invert(lst):
    return [-x for x in lst]
